OL,3,CRising demand at Belfast food kitchen
OL,5,FThe People's Kitchen provides shelter
OL,6,Fand hot meals to those most in need -
OL,7,Fthose fighting drug addictions, others
OL,8,Fwho live in poverty, and people who
OL,9,Fare simply craving company.
OL,11,FIn the season of goodwill, the
OL,12,Fgenerosity of the people of this city
OL,13,Fhasn't gone unnoticed when so many of
OL,14,Fits residents are struggling no matter
OL,15,Ftheir age.
OL,17,FPaul McCusker continued: "The oldest
OL,18,Fman I dealt with recently was 81, who
OL,19,Fwas homeless and the youngest person
OL,20,Flast night on the streets was 18.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/6
